overall property portfolio. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Q92</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Ian Swales:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> KPI5 says, “</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">assessed</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> as non-compliant and having severe defects”. Do you regard a dripping tap as a severe defect?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">James </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Thorburn</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> I am referring to the definitions in the contract. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Q93</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Ian Swales:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> Okay. As the NAO said, this graph stops in August. For KPI5 and KPI6, would we see those orange bars close to the zero line now? 